They said they never figured out
what caused the crash.

757
02:01:11,545 --> 02:01:15,174
Probably some mislabeled
hazardous material caught fire.

758
02:01:19,486 --> 02:01:21,750
So here's where
that ship found you.

759
02:01:23,190 --> 02:01:26,318
You drifted about 500 miles.

760
02:01:26,426 --> 02:01:28,587
This is where your island was,

761
02:01:28,662 --> 02:01:32,098
about 600 miles south of the Cook lslands.

762
02:01:33,667 --> 02:01:35,965
And these are the search grids.

763
02:01:36,036 --> 02:01:38,766
Ships went back and forth
for weeks looking for you.

764
02:01:48,015 --> 02:01:50,040
I never should've gotten on that plane.

765
02:01:52,352 --> 02:01:54,752
I never should've gotten out of the car.

766
02:01:58,658 --> 02:02:00,558
I wanna show you something.

767
02:02:02,696 --> 02:02:04,596
Come here.

768
02:02:14,341 --> 02:02:16,241
This is--
This is our car.

769
02:02:18,578 --> 02:02:20,512
You kept our car.

770
02:02:22,716 --> 02:02:26,049
All right, now, this is weird.

771
02:02:34,494 --> 02:02:36,587
It's a good car.

772
02:02:36,696 --> 02:02:39,096
Had a lot of memories in this car.

773
02:02:39,199 --> 02:02:41,667
Two very nice memories.

774
02:02:41,768 --> 02:02:43,793
Oh, that trip down to the Gulf, yeah.

775
02:02:46,473 --> 02:02:48,373
So, can I drive it ?

776
02:02:48,475 --> 02:02:50,375
It's your car.

777
02:02:58,185 --> 02:03:01,279
That's good, 'cause my--
my taxi's gone.

778
02:03:07,427 --> 02:03:09,691
Um--

779
02:03:09,763 --> 02:03:11,697
Let me get some stuff
out of the back.

780
02:03:34,287 --> 02:03:36,619
You think you're gonna
have more kids ?

781
02:03:36,723 --> 02:03:38,623
I don't know.

782
02:03:38,725 --> 02:03:41,592
It's kind of confusing right now.

783
02:03:41,661 --> 02:03:44,425
Well, you should.

784
02:03:44,498 --> 02:03:46,466
I mean, really, you should.

785
02:03:48,835 --> 02:03:50,769
I would.

786
02:03:52,906 --> 02:03:54,806
So, what now ?

787
02:03:57,878 --> 02:03:59,778
I don't know.

788
02:04:02,415 --> 02:04:04,315
I really don't know.

789
02:04:12,726 --> 02:04:14,660
[ Starts Engine ]

790
02:04:17,130 --> 02:04:18,859
You said you'd be right back.

791
02:04:24,237 --> 02:04:26,171
I'm so sorry.

792
02:04:28,141 --> 02:04:29,870
Me too.

793
02:05:38,845 --> 02:05:40,745
Chuck !

794
02:05:44,684 --> 02:05:47,414
Chuck !

795
02:05:47,520 --> 02:05:49,420
Chuck !

796
02:06:06,706 --> 02:06:08,606
I always knew you were alive.

797
02:06:08,708 --> 02:06:11,370
I knew it.

798
02:06:11,478 --> 02:06:13,571
But everybody said
I had to stop saying that--

799
02:06:13,680 --> 02:06:15,671
that I had to let you go.

800
02:06:17,017 --> 02:06:19,918
I love you.

801
02:06:20,020 --> 02:06:21,885
You're the love of my life.

802
02:06:24,557 --> 02:06:26,457
I love you too, Kelly.

803
02:06:27,994 --> 02:06:29,928
More than you'll ever know.

804
02:07:30,957 --> 02:07:32,857
Chuck ?

805
02:07:39,799 --> 02:07:42,632
You have to go home.

806
02:08:30,917 --> 02:08:32,908
We both had done the math, and--

807
02:08:35,455 --> 02:08:37,753
Kelly added it all up.

808
02:08:39,526 --> 02:08:41,426
She knew she had to let me go.

809
02:08:41,528 --> 02:08:45,794
I added it up, knew that I'd--

810
02:08:45,899 --> 02:08:47,799
I'd lost her.

811
02:08:49,736 --> 02:08:51,897
'Cause I was never gonna
get off that island.

812
02:08:54,941 --> 02:08:57,569
I was gonna die there,

813
02:08:57,677 --> 02:08:59,577
totally alone.

814
02:09:05,952 --> 02:09:08,819
I mean, I was gonna get sick or
I was gonna get injured or something.

815
02:09:12,959 --> 02:09:14,893
The only choice I had,

816
02:09:17,664 --> 02:09:19,859
the only thing I could control...

817
02:09:21,968 --> 02:09:25,495
was when and how...

818
02:09:25,605 --> 02:09:27,505
and where that was gonna happen.

819
02:09:27,607 --> 02:09:31,976
So... I made a rope.

820
02:09:35,048 --> 02:09:37,949
And I went up to the summit
to hang myself.

821
02:09:41,621 --> 02:09:43,680
But I had to test it,
you know ?

822
02:09:43,790 --> 02:09:46,691
Of course.
You know me.

823
02:09:48,661 --> 02:09:50,595
And the weight of the log...

824
02:09:50,663 --> 02:09:53,894
snapped the limb of the tree.

825
02:09:54,000 --> 02:09:55,934
So l-l--

826
02:09:56,002 --> 02:09:58,664
I couldn't even kill myself
the way I wanted to.

827
02:09:58,771 --> 02:10:01,672
I had power over nothing.

828
02:10:10,116 --> 02:10:13,711
And that's when this feeling
came over me like a warm blanket.

829
02:10:17,790 --> 02:10:19,781
I knew...

830
02:10:19,893 --> 02:10:22,123
somehow...

831
02:10:22,195 --> 02:10:24,629
that I had to stay alive.

832
02:10:26,165 --> 02:10:28,065
Somehow.

833
02:10:29,168 --> 02:10:31,534
I had to keep breathing,

834
02:10:34,040 --> 02:10:36,065
even though there was
no reason to hope.

835
02:10:38,211 --> 02:10:41,942
And all my logic said that
I would never see this place again.

836
02:10:46,853 --> 02:10:49,686
So that's what I did.

837
02:10:49,756 --> 02:10:52,190
I stayed alive.

838
02:10:52,292 --> 02:10:54,226
I kept breathing.

839
02:10:56,596 --> 02:10:58,791
And then one day
that logic was proven all wrong,

840
02:10:58,865 --> 02:11:00,799
because the tide...

841
02:11:02,902 --> 02:11:05,336
came in, gave me a sail.

842
02:11:10,076 --> 02:11:12,010
And now, here I am.

843
02:11:15,315 --> 02:11:18,250
I'm back...

844
02:11:18,351 --> 02:11:20,911
in Memphis, talking to you.

845
02:11:23,056 --> 02:11:25,616
I have ice in my glass.

846
02:11:32,231 --> 02:11:34,699
And I've lost her all over again.

847
02:11:42,575 --> 02:11:44,907
I'm so sad that
I don't have Kelly.

848
02:11:50,049 --> 02:11:53,348
But I'm so grateful that
she was with me on that island.

849
02:12:00,693 --> 02:12:02,752
And I know what I have to do now.

850
02:12:05,732 --> 02:12:07,757
I gotta keep breathing.

851
02:12:10,303 --> 02:12:12,863
Because tomorrow, the sun will rise.

852
02:12:14,107 --> 02:12:16,632
Who knows what the tide could bring ?

